# NIX EVAL
Nixpkgs: nixpkgs.nix
Source: https://github.com/NixOS/nix
Description: Evaluate a Nix expression and print the result.
Version: nix --version

## Commands

### Basics
- nix eval --expr "1 + 1": Evaluate a simple arithmetic expression.

### Essentials
- nix eval .#packages.x86_64-linux.hello.name: Evaluate an attribute from a flake.
- nix eval --raw .#packages.x86_64-linux.hello.name: Print result without quotes.

### Intermediaries
- nix eval --json --expr '{ a = 1; }': Evaluate and return as JSON.

### Advanceds
- nix eval --file ./my-file.nix: Evaluate an expression from a standalone file.

### Uncommons
- nix eval --impure --expr "builtins.getEnv "USER"": Allow evaluation of impure functions.

## Tips
- Useful for debugging Nix code and checking attribute values.

## Disclaimers
- Evaluating complex Nix expressions can consume significant memory.

## Alternatives
- nix repl: Interactive evaluation.

